	   <tr><td colspan=2>By the rationale of some of the posters, weight is only 'nice'. In fact for monks it is critical. You should ask your monks how important an item is for them and go by that IMO. It will vary from monk to monk depending on level and existing equipment. if a monk in your guild tells you that an item is the best item they can wear in the game (realisticly) then if it's not for you as a warrior, let the monk have it.<br><br>For example - flayed peabolla legs and oily greaves are just about the best monk legs out there. They should go to monks first. Barbed dragonscale boots are a HUGE improvement for a monk - most monk slippers are ac 7 or below and those are ac 19. No other boots are better. So the monk should have them. Just ask the monk. They know a lot more about their weight problems than a warrior will.<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
