<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=99194457946658></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f99194457946658><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=item.html?item=5413&mid=99194457946658>Monks and Low Weight Items</a> <a id=fs8 href=item.html?item=5413&mid=99194457946658#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=55131><span id=Scholar>Argfeldd</span></a>, <span id=Scholar>Scholar</span><br><span id=notbold>28 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Thu, Jun 7th 4:09 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Why do so many people (particularly monks) think of light equipment as monk equipment?<br><br>Monks operate under a severe weight restriction as all of you no doubt know.&nbsp;&nbsp;I have had to pass on many very nice pieces of equipment simply because they weigh too much. <br><br>Let me ask you this.  If your guild came across a really nice item that could used only by a monk or by whatever your class is and this item weighed 15 pounds, would you be upset if the monk wanted to roll against you for it?  I bet you would be upset.  Obviously he couldn't really use the item even though it says MNK.  How do you think he feels when you roll on that 0.0 weight item after he let you have that nice 15 pound item without argument?  I have an enchanter that carries 60 pounds of equipment.  Weight is not really a factor for him.  If my monk had 60 pounds of gear on, he would get killed by creatures 20 levels below him.  There are some items that are so incredibly nice for monks that they will use them despite their relatively high weight.  To compensate for this, we have to make hard choices in other slots sacrificing AC, stats, and resists so that we can use one or two items that weigh maybe 6 or 7 pounds total.  <br><br>Some light weight items should be considered as exceptions to the "monk gets first crack at light-weight items" rule.  If an item gives 10 ac, 5 hp, and 100 mana, a caster will do more good with it than a monk despite the low weight and nice ac.  Such items have to be considered on a case by case basis.<br><br>Argfeld<br>Level 49 Monk<br>Order of the Scattered Winds<br>Bertoxxulous <br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
