	   <tr><td colspan=2> Look, folks.&nbsp;&nbsp;I'm going to explain this in simple terms so that the slow-brained newbies here can understand it.  <br><br> Low weight is more important for monks than for tank classes.  <br><br> However, high AC is more important for tanks than for monks, because taking damage is a tank's PRIMARY JOB IN THE GROUP.  Sure, every class would like to have AC, but no one needs AC more than a tank.  AC is the number 1 thing a warrior needs, just as int or wis is most important for casters.  This item also has +50 hp.  What are the two most important things for a tank class?  Yup, you got it.  HP and AC.  And this belt has lots of both.  <br><br>  Show me a belt slot item that has higher AC than this.  I can think of only one and that one comes from Dain Frostreaver.  (And morons will complain that that belt shouldn't go to warriors either because it has +mana). <br><br>  <br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
